Reading.js is a crummy bit of CSS and JavaScript that&rsquo;s supposed to make it easier to read long documents online. (Like this one!)
Include two lines in the &lt;head&gt; of a plain HTML file&mdash;the kind produced by pandoc or by most Markdown-to-HTML converters&mdash;and gain nifty features like keyboard shortcuts, section folding, and color scheme switching:
&lt;linkrel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;href=&quot;http://baruffio.com/reading.js/stylesheets/reading.css&quot; /&gt; &lt;scripttype=&quot;text/javascript&quot;src=&quot;http://baruffio.com/reading.js/scripts/reading.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
